bodies = [f'## {sr.title}

{sr.verified_text}' for sr in multi.sections if not sr.dropped_due_to_failure and sr.verified_text]; final_report = f'# {title}

{intro}

{sections_concat}{biblio_section}'. verified_text is the POST-strict_verify string (SectionResult field comment, multi_section_generator.py:1285: 'verified_text: str  # after strict_verify + citation resolution').

For each row in the section's ev_subset it emits EXACTLY:
<<<evidence:{evidence_id}>>>
tier: {tier}
url: {source_url}
statement: {statement}
direct_quote: {direct_quote}
<<<end_evidence>>>
Five fields. Nothing else on the row is passed to the writer — not document_type, not year, not authority_score, not query_origin.
